Ya' know, Chiko,
that is not a bad idea!

00:11:17.427 --> 00:11:21.473 position:50% align:center
[chuckles] Well, obviously.
Anything for my cute big sister.

00:11:21.556 --> 00:11:22.474 position:50% align:center
[ROKO]
You're gross.

00:11:22.557 --> 00:11:23.975 position:50% align:center
[NINA giggles]

00:11:24.059 --> 00:11:25.810 position:50% align:center
Hey, what'd she say?

00:11:25.894 --> 00:11:27.979 position:50% align:center
She said that we
have the approval,

00:11:28.063 --> 00:11:30.190 position:50% align:center
so long as we flash
the audience.

00:11:30.273 --> 00:11:32.359 position:50% align:center
Let's give our ratings a boost!

00:11:32.442 --> 00:11:35.612 position:50% align:center
--[HAYU, NINA groan]
--[ROKO] She's the worst.

00:11:35.695 --> 00:11:37.364 position:50% align:center
Uh, hey, Hemo?

00:11:37.447 --> 00:11:40.492 position:50% align:center
Would you ever come back to
Cat Productions? Just a thought.

00:11:40.575 --> 00:11:41.785 position:50% align:center
[HEMO]
Huh?

00:11:48.667 --> 00:11:49.876 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:11:52.170 --> 00:11:55.090 position:50% align:center
[HAYU]
Finally, battle panties.

00:11:58.760 --> 00:12:00.512 position:50% align:center
[HEMO]
Hmm...

00:12:04.683 --> 00:12:06.518 position:50% align:center
[HEMO giggles]

00:12:06.601 --> 00:12:08.353 position:50% align:center
[HAYU, HEMO] I bought
the same kind as Innochi

00:12:08.436 --> 00:12:10.021 position:50% align:center
in a different color!

00:12:14.693 --> 00:12:15.902 position:50% align:center
[INO]
Hm!

00:12:15.985 --> 00:12:17.195 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:12:17.278 --> 00:12:20.448 position:50% align:center
Oh, my! You look adorable
in your matching sets!

00:12:20.532 --> 00:12:21.825 position:50% align:center
[HAYU, HEMO grumble]

00:12:21.908 --> 00:12:23.118 position:50% align:center
[INO]
Hm?

00:12:24.536 --> 00:12:25.787 position:50% align:center
[TONE]
I'm Tone Honmachi,

00:12:25.870 --> 00:12:27.747 position:50% align:center
a typical high school
freshman and I love idols!

00:12:27.831 --> 00:12:30.166 position:50% align:center
My birthday is October 10th
and my blood type is A.

00:12:30.250 --> 00:12:32.168 position:50% align:center
You can catch me at
an okonomiyaki joint

00:12:32.252 --> 00:12:33.795 position:50% align:center
also called Tone!

00:12:41.052 --> 00:12:43.138 position:50% align:center
[IDOLS]
<i>Dropout Idol Fruit Tart</i> !

00:12:49.269 --> 00:12:51.062 position:50% align:center
What is... all this?

00:12:51.146 --> 00:12:53.023 position:50% align:center
It's meat! So much meat!

00:12:53.106 --> 00:12:54.190 position:50% align:center
It looks so good!

00:12:54.274 --> 00:12:56.901 position:50% align:center
Katsudon breakfast?
Can we afford this?

00:12:56.985 --> 00:12:58.236 position:50% align:center
[HEMO gasps]

00:12:58.319 --> 00:12:59.529 position:50% align:center
[INO giggles]

00:12:59.612 --> 00:13:01.865 position:50% align:center
I told our neighbors we'd
be recording today

00:13:01.948 --> 00:13:04.325 position:50% align:center
and they wanted to support
us and wish us good luck!

00:13:04.409 --> 00:13:06.911 position:50% align:center
The next thing I knew, they
brought us all this yummy food!

00:13:06.995 --> 00:13:08.997 position:50% align:center
[HOHO]
So eat up!

00:13:09.080 --> 00:13:11.624 position:50% align:center
You girls are gonna
need it today!

00:13:11.708 --> 00:13:13.752 position:50% align:center
This is a big opportunity.

00:13:13.835 --> 00:13:15.754 position:50% align:center
Think of it as
battle day to fight

00:13:15.837 --> 00:13:18.131 position:50% align:center
for the Mouse House
Debt Repayment Plan!

00:13:18.214 --> 00:13:19.632 position:50% align:center
Listen up.

00:13:19.716 --> 00:13:22.761 position:50% align:center
If the album you're recording
today isn't successful...

00:13:24.846 --> 00:13:26.931 position:50% align:center
[IDOLS]
Isn't successful?

00:13:27.015 --> 00:13:29.976 position:50% align:center
...you can be sure this will
be the first and last katsudon

00:13:30.060 --> 00:13:31.561 position:50% align:center
you'll ever eat at
the Mouse House.

00:13:31.644 --> 00:13:33.396 position:50% align:center
[IDOLS gasp]

00:13:33.480 --> 00:13:36.649 position:50% align:center
[IDOLS]
N-No!

00:13:45.325 --> 00:13:47.327 position:50% align:center
[IDOLS gasp]

00:13:47.410 --> 00:13:49.329 position:50% align:center
Okay! Ino's first!

00:13:49.412 --> 00:13:50.705 position:50% align:center
Come on inside!

00:13:50.789 --> 00:13:51.790 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:13:51.873 --> 00:13:53.708 position:50% align:center
Oh, okay!

00:13:53.792 --> 00:13:56.711 position:50% align:center
I-I'll do my best!

00:13:58.588 --> 00:14:01.925 position:50% align:center
[HOHO] Huh? This reminds
of me something.

00:14:02.008 --> 00:14:03.343 position:50% align:center
[HOHO whimpers]

00:14:03.426 --> 00:14:05.220 position:50% align:center
[HOHO]
Now I'm feeling anxious!

00:14:05.303 --> 00:14:07.764 position:50% align:center
--[RIRI] Hoho, look!
--[HOHO] Huh?

00:14:07.847 --> 00:14:09.140 position:50% align:center
[RIRI giggles]

00:14:09.224 --> 00:14:11.309 position:50% align:center
I bought myself a new school
uniform with my bonus!

00:14:11.393 --> 00:14:12.936 position:50% align:center
[HOHO growls]

00:14:13.019 --> 00:14:15.814 position:50% align:center
[HOHO] I have to focus,
I can't lose my cool!

00:14:15.897 --> 00:14:17.357 position:50% align:center
Today is important.

00:14:17.440 --> 00:14:19.109 position:50% align:center
The outcome of this
session determines

00:14:19.192 --> 00:14:22.028 position:50% align:center
whether or not the Mouse
House debt will be repaid!

00:14:22.112 --> 00:14:23.530 position:50% align:center
[SOUND GUY A]
We're ready to go in here.

00:14:23.613 --> 00:14:25.990 position:50% align:center
Just, uh, you know, sing like
you normally would, okay?

00:14:26.074 --> 00:14:27.158 position:50% align:center
Okay!

00:14:27.242 --> 00:14:31.496 position:50% align:center
♪

00:14:31.579 --> 00:14:33.123 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:14:33.206 --> 00:14:35.625 position:50% align:center
Ino, don't be so
hard on yourself.

00:14:35.709 --> 00:14:37.377 position:50% align:center
First time nerves
are totally normal.

00:14:37.460 --> 00:14:40.880 position:50% align:center
But when it was finally time
to record, I just froze up!

00:14:40.964 --> 00:14:42.132 position:50% align:center
Oh, well.

00:14:42.215 --> 00:14:43.925 position:50% align:center
So, did you have better
luck than she did?

00:14:44.009 --> 00:14:45.677 position:50% align:center
Me?! Well, I uh...!

00:14:45.760 --> 00:14:48.179 position:50% align:center
It was going fine...

00:14:48.263 --> 00:14:49.347 position:50% align:center
...until the smell.

00:14:49.431 --> 00:14:51.433 position:50% align:center
Huh? What smell?

00:14:51.516 --> 00:14:53.143 position:50% align:center
[NINA]
Um, never mind!

00:14:53.226 --> 00:14:54.728 position:50% align:center
I don't want to
talk about it!

00:14:54.811 --> 00:14:56.104 position:50% align:center
[NINA]
I can't say it!

00:14:56.187 --> 00:14:57.647 position:50% align:center
They can't know that I
messed up because I was

00:14:57.731 --> 00:15:00.525 position:50% align:center
distracted by how good
the room smelled!

00:15:00.608 --> 00:15:03.486 position:50% align:center
So that means... you guys
will have to rerecord.

00:15:03.570 --> 00:15:05.280 position:50% align:center
Wonder how Hayu is
doing right now?

00:15:05.363 --> 00:15:06.614 position:50% align:center
Oh, she's fine!

00:15:06.698 --> 00:15:09.534 position:50% align:center
I mean, she started out as
a musician, remember?

00:15:09.617 --> 00:15:10.994 position:50% align:center
--I'm sure she's doing great!
--[door clatters]

00:15:11.077 --> 00:15:12.078 position:50% align:center
[ROKO, NINA, INO]
Huh?

00:15:12.162 --> 00:15:15.331 position:50% align:center
[INO] Gah! What happened
in there? Hayu!

00:15:18.001 --> 00:15:19.753 position:50% align:center
They got really mad
at me and told me

00:15:19.836 --> 00:15:21.546 position:50% align:center
I wasn't matching
everyone else.

00:15:21.629 --> 00:15:24.549 position:50% align:center
And... they told me that
I had to be more aware

00:15:24.632 --> 00:15:25.800 position:50% align:center
because I was pitchy.

00:15:25.884 --> 00:15:28.428 position:50% align:center
I was told to focus and
not get distracted.

00:15:28.511 --> 00:15:29.888 position:50% align:center
What'd they tell you two?

00:15:29.971 --> 00:15:32.057 position:50% align:center
That my voice was too weak
to be heard over the music.

00:15:32.140 --> 00:15:33.475 position:50% align:center
They told me I was too loud

00:15:33.558 --> 00:15:35.935 position:50% align:center
and needed to stop
moving around so much.

00:15:36.019 --> 00:15:36.811 position:50% align:center
Moving?

00:15:36.895 --> 00:15:38.521 position:50% align:center
Yeah. During the session,

00:15:38.605 --> 00:15:41.024 position:50% align:center
my bladder wasn't
cooperating with me.

00:15:41.107 --> 00:15:42.734 position:50% align:center
[whines]

00:15:42.817 --> 00:15:43.943 position:50% align:center
What can I say?

00:15:44.027 --> 00:15:46.529 position:50% align:center
When I get nervous,
it makes me need to go!

00:15:46.613 --> 00:15:50.200 position:50% align:center
In fact, just thinking
about it my bladder is...!

00:15:50.283 --> 00:15:51.659 position:50% align:center
[ROKO]
Go to the bathroom!

00:15:51.743 --> 00:15:54.913 position:50% align:center
[toilet flushes]

00:15:54.996 --> 00:15:58.249 position:50% align:center
[INO]
Ah... I feel much better now.

00:15:58.333 --> 00:15:59.709 position:50% align:center
[INO]
That was embarrassing.

00:15:59.793 --> 00:16:01.836 position:50% align:center
Maybe I should try
to drink less water?

00:16:01.920 --> 00:16:03.630 position:50% align:center
No. I just need to stay calm,

00:16:03.713 --> 00:16:05.507 position:50% align:center
but I never know when
my nerves will strike!

00:16:05.590 --> 00:16:08.551 position:50% align:center
Or, should I learn how
to hold it in better?

00:16:08.635 --> 00:16:09.511 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:16:09.594 --> 00:16:10.887 position:50% align:center
[INO]
Wh-What am I thinking?

00:16:10.970 --> 00:16:13.515 position:50% align:center
It's totally unhealthy
to hold it in!

00:16:13.598 --> 00:16:14.891 position:50% align:center
Miss Ino?

00:16:14.974 --> 00:16:17.435 position:50% align:center
Um, did you say, "hold it in"?

00:16:17.519 --> 00:16:21.106 position:50% align:center
[INO gasps] Oh, no! It's not--
It's not what you think!

00:16:21.189 --> 00:16:24.025 position:50% align:center
I'm just brainstorming for
the next time this happens!

00:16:24.109 --> 00:16:25.610 position:50% align:center
[HEMO]
Oh.

00:16:25.694 --> 00:16:29.781 position:50% align:center
You see, I can totally relate.
I always hold my feelings in.

00:16:29.864 --> 00:16:32.200 position:50% align:center
Can we talk about
this someplace else?

00:16:33.243 --> 00:16:36.079 position:50% align:center
So, have your nerves
always been directly

00:16:36.162 --> 00:16:37.247 position:50% align:center
connected to your bladder?

00:16:37.330 --> 00:16:38.707 position:50% align:center
It's embarrassing,

00:16:38.790 --> 00:16:41.710 position:50% align:center
but it's been like this for
as long as I can remember.

00:16:41.793 --> 00:16:43.545 position:50% align:center
During class presentations...

00:16:43.628 --> 00:16:45.630 position:50% align:center
During sports events...

00:16:45.714 --> 00:16:47.716 position:50% align:center
It happens like clockwork
anytime I perform

00:16:47.799 --> 00:16:48.967 position:50% align:center
in front of people.

00:16:49.050 --> 00:16:50.677 position:50% align:center
[HEMO] Does this count
as having some strange

00:16:50.760 --> 00:16:52.929 position:50% align:center
kind of super power?

00:16:53.013 --> 00:16:54.764 position:50% align:center
Oh yeah. Come to think of it,

00:16:54.848 --> 00:16:57.434 position:50% align:center
this happened to you
at our concert, too!

00:16:57.517 --> 00:16:58.643 position:50% align:center
Tell us the truth.

00:16:58.727 --> 00:17:00.145 position:50% align:center
Did you pee your pants
that day on stage--

00:17:00.228 --> 00:17:02.397 position:50% align:center
I did not pee on stage!

00:17:02.480 --> 00:17:05.775 position:50% align:center
I'm able to hold it in
most of the time, okay?

00:17:05.859 --> 00:17:08.945 position:50% align:center
[IDOLS]
Only... most of the time?

00:17:09.029 --> 00:17:12.449 position:50% align:center
Ugh! This isn't the time or
place for this conversation.

00:17:12.532 --> 00:17:14.743 position:50% align:center
We need to turn this
recording session around!

00:17:14.826 --> 00:17:16.119 position:50% align:center
She does have a point.

00:17:16.202 --> 00:17:17.412 position:50% align:center
None of us were successful.

00:17:17.495 --> 00:17:19.122 position:50% align:center
We all have to re-record.

00:17:19.205 --> 00:17:20.373 position:50% align:center
[HAYU sighs]

00:17:20.457 --> 00:17:22.375 position:50% align:center
No more feeling
sorry for ourselves.

00:17:22.459 --> 00:17:25.253 position:50% align:center
We need to start brainstorming
ideas on how to improve.

00:17:25.337 --> 00:17:27.547 position:50% align:center
Now, speak up!
Which one of you has a plan?

00:17:27.630 --> 00:17:29.299 position:50% align:center
[IDOLS]
Mmmm.

00:17:29.382 --> 00:17:31.343 position:50% align:center
Wait! How about
pitch correction?

00:17:31.426 --> 00:17:33.720 position:50% align:center
They can fix our voices using
one of those programs!

00:17:33.803 --> 00:17:35.597 position:50% align:center
Absolutely not!

00:17:35.680 --> 00:17:38.808 position:50% align:center
[CHIKO giggles] It sounds like
you need some help, big sister.

00:17:38.892 --> 00:17:41.144 position:50% align:center
No! Don't tell me.

00:17:41.227 --> 00:17:43.229 position:50% align:center
[CHIKO]
There's a trick to singing well.

00:17:43.313 --> 00:17:45.440 position:50% align:center
How would you all like a lesson?

00:17:46.649 --> 00:17:48.360 position:50% align:center
[ROKO]
Cream Anmitsu?

00:17:48.443 --> 00:17:49.652 position:50% align:center
[CHIKO giggles]

00:17:51.738 --> 00:17:54.449 position:50% align:center
Yeah, so anyway, we need
to figure out some ideas.

00:17:54.532 --> 00:17:57.619 position:50% align:center
[CHIKO] Um, hello? Your super
famous sister is here?

00:17:57.702 --> 00:17:59.204 position:50% align:center
Whatever.

00:17:59.287 --> 00:18:02.207 position:50% align:center
I had a feeling Cream Anmitsu
would be here when I saw Riri.

00:18:02.290 --> 00:18:04.292 position:50% align:center
The only reason we get
to record here today

00:18:04.376 --> 00:18:06.336 position:50% align:center
is cause you
already were, right?

00:18:06.419 --> 00:18:09.214 position:50% align:center
[RIRI giggles]
She figured us out!

00:18:09.297 --> 00:18:11.341 position:50% align:center
You do the same
thing every time!

00:18:11.424 --> 00:18:14.219 position:50% align:center
How much longer until you try
something new for a change?

00:18:14.302 --> 00:18:17.055 position:50% align:center
Big sister! You don't
have to be so mean!

00:18:17.138 --> 00:18:19.891 position:50% align:center
Now, now. There's nothing
wrong with accepting help

00:18:19.974 --> 00:18:21.101 position:50% align:center
from time to time.

00:18:21.184 --> 00:18:23.812 position:50% align:center
As idols, you should be
kind to one another.

00:18:23.895 --> 00:18:25.563 position:50% align:center
And lest we forget.

00:18:25.647 --> 00:18:29.693 position:50% align:center
Sisters like you two
are incredibly special.

00:18:29.776 --> 00:18:31.236 position:50% align:center
Hoho...

00:18:31.319 --> 00:18:33.697 position:50% align:center
Could you stop staring
at us like that please?

00:18:33.780 --> 00:18:34.823 position:50% align:center
[HOHO]
Uh...

00:18:34.906 --> 00:18:37.450 position:50% align:center
A-Anyway, just hear me out.

00:18:37.534 --> 00:18:39.661 position:50% align:center
The younger sister
is a popular idol!

00:18:39.744 --> 00:18:42.372 position:50% align:center
The older sister is
an unpopular idol!

00:18:42.455 --> 00:18:44.207 position:50% align:center
Now, they're forced to compete.

00:18:44.290 --> 00:18:47.419 position:50% align:center
And only one can become
the world's biggest star!

00:18:47.502 --> 00:18:50.130 position:50% align:center
It's a rivalry for the ages!

00:18:50.213 --> 00:18:51.798 position:50% align:center
You can't blame me
for taking advantage

00:18:51.881 --> 00:18:53.383 position:50% align:center
of your unique situation!

00:18:53.466 --> 00:18:57.137 position:50% align:center
As a producer, I have to
jump on this opportunity!

00:18:57.220 --> 00:19:00.390 position:50% align:center
[RIRI]
Wow! Hoho, you're so amazing!

00:19:00.473 --> 00:19:04.144 position:50% align:center
She really is passionate. Is
your producer always like this?

00:19:04.227 --> 00:19:06.187 position:50% align:center
Well first off,
she's our manager,

00:19:06.271 --> 00:19:09.899 position:50% align:center
so I don't know where all this
producer talk is coming from.

00:19:09.983 --> 00:19:11.526 position:50% align:center
Anyway, since you offered,

00:19:11.609 --> 00:19:13.945 position:50% align:center
what was that singing trick
you wanted to tell me about?

00:19:14.029 --> 00:19:15.363 position:50% align:center
What? Oh!

00:19:15.447 --> 00:19:18.199 position:50% align:center
Well, maybe the trick to signing
well is to think about

00:19:18.283 --> 00:19:20.201 position:50% align:center
something that
you love, you know?

00:19:20.285 --> 00:19:22.454 position:50% align:center
Nua, Rua, anything to add?

00:19:22.537 --> 00:19:23.538 position:50% align:center
[NUA, RUA]
Uh!

00:19:23.621 --> 00:19:25.999 position:50% align:center
No way. Don't look
to me for advice.

00:19:26.082 --> 00:19:29.502 position:50% align:center
The reason I'm so good...
is that I was born talented!

00:19:29.586 --> 00:19:32.213 position:50% align:center
Well, let me see.

00:19:32.297 --> 00:19:33.173 position:50% align:center
Here you go.

00:19:33.256 --> 00:19:34.507 position:50% align:center
[ROKO]
Ah. Great.

00:19:34.591 --> 00:19:37.344 position:50% align:center
Thanks for this completely
unhelpful gesture.

00:19:37.427 --> 00:19:39.387 position:50% align:center
You know, maybe it
is a good idea

00:19:39.471 --> 00:19:40.722 position:50% align:center
to think about
something we love!

00:19:40.805 --> 00:19:43.224 position:50% align:center
Yeah! It could be just
the thing we need!

00:19:43.308 --> 00:19:45.268 position:50% align:center
[ROKO]
Something we love...

00:19:47.062 --> 00:19:48.897 position:50% align:center
I'm having a
little trouble, Nina.

00:19:48.980 --> 00:19:50.774 position:50% align:center
Can I borrow you for a second?

00:19:50.857 --> 00:19:52.859 position:50% align:center
[INO, HAYU]
Huh?

00:19:52.942 --> 00:19:55.153 position:50% align:center
I'm just finding
it hard to decide.

00:19:55.236 --> 00:19:57.864 position:50% align:center
How are you sure if you
really love something?

00:19:57.947 --> 00:19:59.866 position:50% align:center
Isn't that a big
question to ask?

00:19:59.949 --> 00:20:01.493 position:50% align:center
It is pretty vague.

00:20:01.576 --> 00:20:02.744 position:50% align:center
So, what do you guys think?

00:20:02.827 --> 00:20:03.995 position:50% align:center
[INO, HAYU]
What?

00:20:04.079 --> 00:20:05.538 position:50% align:center
[INO] I can't tell if
she's serious or not,

00:20:05.622 --> 00:20:08.291 position:50% align:center
but it looks like she knows
exactly what she loves!

